Hi, Sarat,

I would highly recommend:

- Working Effectively with Legacy Code
    by Michael Feathers
- Refactoring: Improving the Design of Existing Code
    by Martin Fowler, Kent Beck, John Brant, William Opdyke, Don Roberts
- Refactoring to Patterns
    by Joshua Kerievsky

In fact, I&#39;d recommend ALL of them, but if you have to pace yourself,
I&#39;d suggest them in the above order.  All are excellent, but it sounds
as if the first one is closest to &quot;hands-on&quot; immediate application to
your need.

Good luck!
-jn-

